sentences: Ursula Oppens (born February 2, 1944) is an American classical concert pianist and educator.
Ursula Oppens was born on February 2, 1944 in New York City into a highly musical family.
She obtained a high school diploma from the Brearley School (1961) a Bachelor of Arts degree (cum laude) from Radcliffe College (1965) and an M.S. degree from the Juilliard School (1967).

Interview with Ursula Oppens, April 29, 1990
Ursula Oppens is renowned for her commissioning and championship of the music of American composers who were born predominantly in the early decades of the 20th century.
From 1994 until 2008 Oppens was on the summer faculty of the Tanglewood Music Center.

Oppens's discography includes a recording on Vanguard of Frederic Rzewski's "The People United Will Never Be Defeated" and a version on American Piano Music of Our Time of Elliott Carter's Night Fantasies.
